Create a new RelationalDatasetConnector object

relational_dataset_connector.Rd

Create RelationalDatasetConnector from callable_function.

Please note that the script has to end with a call creating desired object. The error will be raised otherwise.

rcd_dataset_connector - Create a RelationalDatasetConnector from any R function.

rds_dataset_connector - Create a RelationalDatasetConnector from RDS file.

script_dataset_connector - Create a RelationalDatasetConnector from .R file.

code_dataset_connector - Create a RelationalDatasetConnector from a string of code.

rice_dataset_connector - Create a RelationalDatasetConnector from RICE dataset.

teradata_dataset_connector - Create a RelationalDatasetConnector from TERADATA dataset

csv_dataset_connector - Create a RelationalDatasetConnector from csv (or general delimited file).

rds_cdisc_dataset_connector - Create a RelationalDatasetConnector from RDS file with keys automatically assigned by dataname

rcd_cdisc_dataset_connector - Create a DatasetConnector from any R function with keys assigned automatically by dataname.

rice_cdisc_dataset_connector - Create a RelationalDatasetConnector from RICE dataset with keys assigned automatically by dataname.

script_cdisc_dataset_connector - Create a RelationalDatasetConnector from script file with keys assigned automatically by dataname.

code_cdisc_dataset_connector - Create a RelationalDatasetConnector from a string of code with keys assigned automatically by dataname.

teradata_cdisc_dataset_connector - Create a RelationalDatasetConnector from TERADATA dataset with keys assigned automatically by dataname.

csv_cdisc_dataset_connector - Create a RelationalDatasetConnector from csv (or general delimited) file with keys assigned automatically by dataname.

fun_dataset_connector - Create a RelationalDatasetConnector from function and its arguments.

fun_cdisc_dataset_connector - Create a RelationalDatasetConnector from function and its arguments with keys assigned automatically by dataname.

relational_dataset_connector(
  dataname,
  pull_callable,
  keys,
  code = character(0),
  script = character(0),
  label = character(0),
  vars = list()
)

Arguments

dataname

(character)
A given name for the dataset it may not contain spaces
pull_callable

(CallableFunction)
function with necessary arguments set to fetch data from connection.
keys

(keys)
object of S3 class keys containing foreign, primary keys and parent information
code

(character)
String containing the code to produce the object. The code must end in a call to the object.
script

(character)
Alternatively to code - location of the file containing modification code. Can't be used simultaneously with script.
label

(character)
Label to describe the dataset.
vars

(named list)
In case when this object code depends on the raw_data from the other NamedDataset, NamedDatasetConnector object(s) or other constant value, this/these object(s) should be included. Please note that vars are included to this object as local vars and they cannot be modified within another dataset.
path

(character)
path to the file
fun

(function)
any R function which generates data.frame, especially functions from random.cdisc.data like radsl
...

(optional)
additional arguments applied to pull function (readr::read_delim) by default delim = ",".
file

(character)
path to (.csv) (or general delimited) file that contains data.frame object
mutate_code

(character)
String containing the code used to mutate the object after it is produced.
table

(character) table name
func

(function)
a custom function to obtain dataset.
func_args

(list)
additional arguments for (func)
.

Value

new RelationalDatasetConnector object

RelationalDatasetConnector object

Examples

# simple example
file_example <- tempfile(fileext = ".R")
writeLines(
  text = c(
    "library(teal)
     library(random.cdisc.data)

     pull_callable <- callable_function(radsl)
     pull_callable$set_args(list(cached = TRUE))
     relational_dataset_connector(\"ADSL\", pull_callable, get_cdisc_keys(\"ADSL\"))"
  ),
  con = file_example
)
x <- relational_dataset_connector_file(file_example)
get_code(x)
#> [1] "ADSL <- radsl(cached = TRUE)"
library(random.cdisc.data)
x <- rcd_dataset_connector(
  dataname = "ADSL",
  fun = radsl,
  keys = get_cdisc_keys("ADSL"),
  cached = TRUE
)
x$get_code()

library(random.cdisc.data)
x <- code_dataset_connector(
  dataname = "ADSL",
  keys = get_cdisc_keys("ADSL"),
  code = "ADSL <- radsl(cached = TRUE); ADSL"
)

x$get_code()
#> [1] "ADSL <- radsl(cached = TRUE)\nADSL <- ADSL"

mutate_dataset(x, code = "ADSL$new_variable <- 1")
x$get_code()
#> [1] "ADSL <- radsl(cached = TRUE)\nADSL <- ADSL\nADSL$new_variable <- 1"

file_example <- tempfile(fileext = ".R")
writeLines(
  text = c(
    "seed <- 1; ADSL <- radsl(cached = TRUE, seed = seed)\nADSL"
  ),
  con = file_example
)

y <- code_dataset_connector(
  dataname = "ADSL",
  keys = get_cdisc_keys("ADSL"),
  code = paste0(readLines(file_example), collapse = "\n")
)

if (FALSE) {
my_data <- function(...) {
  # whatever code
  set.seed(1234)
  library(MASS)
  require(dplyr)
  x <- data.frame(
    STUDYID = 1,
    USUBJID = 1:40,
    z = stats::rnorm(40),
    zz = factor(sample(letters[1:3], 40, replace = TRUE)),
    NAs = rep(NA, 40)
  )
  x$w <- as.numeric(MASS::mvrnorm(40, 0, 1))
  x$ww <- as.numeric(MASS::mvrnorm(40, 0, 1))
  rtables::var_labels(x) <- c("STUDYID", "USUBJID", "z", "zz", "NAs", "w", "ww")
  x
}
y <- fun_cdisc_dataset_connector(
  dataname = "ADSL",
  func = my_data
)

y$get_code()

y$pull()

get_raw_data(y)
}
